Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 21:33:24 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 42/43] DimmerWindow: PiP-style fling-then-spring animation for
 mini window
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the OverScroller rebound/snap fling animation with a two-phase
fling-then-spring system that mimics PiP's PhysicsAnimator behavior.

Phase 1 (fling): OverScroller.fling() provides friction-based inertia
deceleration, tracking velocity via multi-frame averaging for stability.

Phase 2 (spring): When the fling hits a horizontal edge, a damped
spring simulation takes over — X uses critical damping (ζ=1.0) for
smooth edge settle, Y uses light damping (ζ=0.78) for a subtle arc.
The spring target Y is the fling's end position (not the start),
creating a parabolic compound motion on both axes.

All animation runs on the UI thread via ValueAnimator, matching the
touch handling code path for zero cross-thread issues.
